        "content": "### üìã Embedded Remote Desktop Access\n\nThis panel provides access to a remote **LXDE desktop environment** running inside a Docker container via **noVNC**. Use this interface to:\n\n- Interact with graphical applications installed in the container (e.g., logic analyzer tools, browser, IDEs).\n- Run embedded development tools like `minicom`, `openocd`, and `PulseView`.\n- Monitor or debug hardware via USB-connected interfaces inside the container.\n\n> üñ•Ô∏è The noVNC session runs over HTTP and requires no separate VNC viewer ‚Äî it works directly in your browser. \n\n> The noVNC session can be modified by altering the Dockerfile which builds it.\n\n---\n\n#### üõ†Ô∏è Troubleshooting Tips\n\n- If the screen is black or fails to load:\n  - Ensure the container is running.\n  - Verify the noVNC service is reachable on the configured port.\n  - Check browser console for blocked content (CORS, HTTPS mismatch, etc.).\n",
